 <!--This is a Javascript phone book app.

     The user is presented with a HTML drop down list object...
     from which they are able to select a name.

     Then, when they 'click' on the button:
     [Phone number]
     ...the program displays what is the 'selected' name phone number.

     ----

     NOTE(S): 

     DATA Storage: 
        Both 'names/phone numbers'...
        are all written/stored inside of the 
        HTML drop down list select object.
        (This is the 'simplest'..; though, probably, NOT the most 'efficient' way to both 'store/retrieve' data.)

     CODE CREATION:
        There are, in fact, two versions of this program...

        I first started developing this app. inside of CodePen.io:

        - https://codepen.io/paulramnora/pen/KwdRJWR

        ...then, finding a number of bugs there...decided it might be far better working offline, instead.
        Later on, I returned back to develop the app at CodePen.io...until when I had a fully working application.

        Next, I continued working offline...until the offline application worked, too;
        finally, I decided to upload the 'source code' into my GitHub online a/c.: Javascript repository.
 -->

